                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Beta ʾƎsrāʾel prayers,  apparently destined for the Seventh Sabbath. Fol. 1a. Various prayers starting with "Heaken Israel". The prayers contain numerous Agau elements. There are, interspersed among the prayers, itations from the Teezaza Sanbat. In 2b Abba Sabra and Abba Sega are named as authors. -- 8a. The same prayers as in the Saatat manuscript, no.23, pages 48-226. -- 20a. Canticles and prayers of the Prophets. -- 27b. Probably a chapter of the book of Enoch -- 34a. Ezra Apocalypse -- 56a. Alphabetic prayers, disposed according to the Hebrew Alphabet
                        </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <locus from="1r"/>
                            <title>Various prayers starting with "Heaken Israel"</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
